TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Dynamics of Dealer Markets Under Competition
AU  - HO, THOMAS S. Y.
AU  - STOLL, HANS R.
Y1  - 1983/09/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1983.tb02282.x
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 1053
EP  - 1074
VL  - 38
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1983.tb02282.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT The behavior of competing dealers in securities markets is analyzed. Securities are characterized by stochastic returns and stochastic transactions. Reservation bid and ask prices of dealers are derived under alternative assumptions about the degree to which transactions are correlated across stocks at a given time and over time in a given stock. The conditions for interdealer trading are specified, and the equilibrium distribution of dealer inventories and the equilibrium market spread are derived. Implications for the structure of securities markets are examined.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Relation Between Common Stock Returns Trading Activity and Market Value
AU  - JAMES, CHRISTOPHER
AU  - EDMISTER, ROBERT O.
Y1  - 1983/09/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1983.tb02283.x
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 1075
EP  - 1086
VL  - 38
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1983.tb02283.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT This study examines the relation between common stock returns, trading activity and market value. Our results indicate that although firm size and trading activity are highly correlated, differences in trading activity are not the underlying reason for the firm size anomaly, the finding of systematic differences in risk adjusted returns across stocks of firms of different size.
ER  - 

